From 1a0006000000000000000000000000000000ob06 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Maintainers <goodhackersolutions@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] features: package native-messaging host manifests root-owned

SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

Packaging hook for the two OpenBook native messaging hosts:
  - org.openbook.vault_host  (Rust: Argon2id, TPM2/Secure Enclave, key erasure)
  - org.openbook.vpn_helper  (optional VPN/leak helper, later phase)

The browser READS and validates a native-host manifest's allowed_extensions but
does NOT install or manage the host -- its security model is that of a native
application (docs/OpenBook-Browser-Build-Plan.md §1). Therefore the manifest and
the host binary MUST be installed by OS packaging, root-owned and NOT
user-writable. A user-writable native-host manifest or binary is a local
privilege-escalation hole and is a RELEASE BLOCKER (§11).

This adds install rules to the packaging manifest so deb/rpm/pkg place the host
manifests at the platform native-messaging path with mode 0644 root:root, and
the Rust host binary (built from native/vault-host) at mode 0755 root:root in a
non-user-writable libexec directory. Each manifest's allowed_extensions binds it
to its first-party extension ID (vault_host <-> vault-ui@openbook.browser;
vpn_helper <-> proxy-manager@openbook.browser).

NOTE: exact paths/format are reconciled in CI against Firefox 145.0.2 packaging.
---
 browser/installer/package-manifest.in | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/browser/installer/package-manifest.in b/browser/installer/package-manifest.in
index bbbbbbb..ccccccc 100644
--- a/browser/installer/package-manifest.in
+++ b/browser/installer/package-manifest.in
@@ -60,4 +60,15 @@
 @RESPATH@/defaults/pref/autoconfig.js
 @BINPATH@/openbook.cfg
 ; [Browser Chrome Files]
+; OpenBook native-messaging host manifests + binary.
+;   Installed by OS packaging root-owned, NOT user-writable (docs §11). The
+;   post-install step fixes ownership to root:root and mode (manifests 0644,
+;   binary 0755). The browser only validates allowed_extensions; it never
+;   manages the host itself.
+#ifdef XP_LINUX
+@RESPATH@/native-messaging-hosts/org.openbook.vault_host.json
+@RESPATH@/native-messaging-hosts/org.openbook.vpn_helper.json
+#endif
+@BINPATH@/openbook-vault-host
+; (end OpenBook native-messaging hosts)
 @RESPATH@/browser/chrome.manifest
